href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjections</fr:link></fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="marcelofiore.xml"
type="local"
addr="marcelofiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The projection function <fr:tex>\pi _1 \colon  A \times  B \to  A</fr:tex> sending <fr:tex>{ \mathopen {} \left ( a,b \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> to <fr:tex>a</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjective</fr:link> if and only if either <html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex>B  \not = \varnothing</fr:tex></html:span> or <fr:tex>A= \varnothing</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3140</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#388</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-388.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="marcelofiore.xml"
type="local"
addr="marcelofiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00MC</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Suppose that <fr:tex>\pi _1 \colon  A \times  B \to  A</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjective</fr:link>. We proceed by cases on whether <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is empty:</fr:p>
 <fr:ol><fr:li>If <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is empty, we are done.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>If <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is inhabited by some <fr:tex>a \in  A</fr:tex>, then by assumption there exists <fr:tex>u \in  A \times  B</fr:tex> such that <fr:tex>\pi _1 { \mathopen {} \left ( u \right ) \mathclose {}} =a</fr:tex>. Thus <fr:tex>B</fr:tex> is inhabited by <fr:tex>\pi _2 { \mathopen {} \left ( u \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>

 <fr:p>Conversely, suppose that either <fr:tex>B \not = \varnothing</fr:tex> or <fr:tex>A= \varnothing</fr:tex>. Fixing <fr:tex>a \in  A</fr:tex>, we must show that there exists <fr:tex>u \in  A \times  B</fr:tex> such that <fr:tex>\pi _1 { \mathopen {} \left ( u \right ) \mathclose {}} =a</fr:tex>. If <fr:tex>A= \varnothing</fr:tex>, then we have a contradiction already; on the other hand, if there exists any <fr:tex>b \in  B</fr:tex>, we may define <fr:tex>u:= { \mathopen {} \left ( a,b \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> and we are done.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
