type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjection</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3146</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#387</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-387.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="marcelofiore.xml"
type="local"
addr="marcelofiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00MD</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>For the <fr:link
href="jms-00KI.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KI">identity function</fr:link> on a set <fr:tex>A</fr:tex>, we must check that for all <fr:tex>a \in  A</fr:tex>, there exists an element <fr:tex>a' \in  A</fr:tex> such that <fr:tex>a'=a</fr:tex>. Of course, we choose <fr:tex>a' := a</fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex>f \colon  A \twoheadrightarrow  B</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>g \colon  B \twoheadrightarrow  C</fr:tex> be two <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjections</fr:link>. To show that <fr:tex>g \circ  f \colon  A \to  C</fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjection</fr:link>, we fix <fr:tex>c \in  C</fr:tex> to exhibit some <fr:tex>a \in  A</fr:tex> such that <fr:tex>g { \mathopen {} \left ( f { \mathopen {} \left ( a \right ) \mathclose {}} \right ) \mathclose {}}  = c</fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex>g \colon  B \twoheadrightarrow  C</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjective</fr:link>, there exists <fr:tex>b \in  B</fr:tex> such that <fr:tex>g { \mathopen {} \left ( b \right ) \mathclose {}}  = c</fr:tex>. Becuase <fr:tex>f \colon  A \twoheadrightarrow  B</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjective</fr:link>, there exists <fr:tex>a \in  A</fr:tex> such that <fr:tex>f { \mathopen {} \left ( a \right ) \mathclose {}}  = b</fr:tex>. Thus we have <fr:tex>g { \mathopen {} \left ( f { \mathopen {} \left ( a \right ) \mathclose {}} \right ) \mathclose {}} =g { \mathopen {} \left ( b \right ) \mathclose {}} =c</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
